timeline.bodyText:
The future chaining here is making life much more complex than it needs to be.  First, get the head, then when you have the head, decide if it's before min genesis and call the right method.  Right now you're starting the process to get head, then queuing up the process to decide if it's before or after, then queuing up the decision of which method to call etc.
It should just be:
  public void start() {
    getHead().thenCompose(headBlock -> {
      if (isHeadBeforeMinGenesis(headBlock)) {
        return headBeforeMinGenesisMode(headBlock);
      } else {
        return headAfterMinGenesisMode(headBlock);
      }
    });
  }

and isHeadBeforeMinGenesis, headBeforeMinGenesisMode and headAfterMinGenesisMode all take a EthBlock.Block rather than a SafeFuture<EthBlock.Block>.  Now life is easy. :)
The other detail is that you need to handle errors - mostly if getHead fails or the requests for deposits in headBeforeMinGenesisMode and headAfterMinGenesisMode fails.

